<p>I cannot compare it with XMPP, but I am happy with Matrix for chatting. You should just do everything what is recommended when making an account. The on-boarding suggests you can do it later, that is where many problems come from, at least for me and some people I know.</p>

<p>Jitsi is great for talking to a few students. I prefer BigBlueButton, especially for larger groups. https://bigbluebutton.org</p>

<p>The next stage of FOSS mastery is to embed BBB in a H5P homepage. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H5P</p>
